The paper deals with probabilistic models and inference algorithms, which are commonly studied in the fields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of symmetries in probabilistic models is also a topic of interest in database systems (cs.DB) and combinatorial optimization (cs.CC). The paper also discusses the complexity of conditioning on evidence, which is a fundamental problem in probabilistic inference and can be related to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
